{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, a differentiable solver (i.e., differentiable physics) has to be employed.",
    "This significantly outperforms the purely supervised approach, where the entire coarse trajectory is applied without corrections in between.",
    "The number of steps performed is a hyperparameter, which increases the accuracy but comes with a higher computational effort.",
    "This concept is referred to as solver-in-the-loop.Further variations perform the coarse-to-fine mapping in a patch-based manner, where the interfaces require a special treatment [493].",
    "Another approach uses a NN to map the coarse solution to the closest fine solution stored in a database [494]."
  ]
}